<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="119" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="119">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Sparkia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sparkia immacula" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="immacula">Sparkia immacula</taxonomicName>
is known from Arizona and New Mexico. Adult flight dates are 20 June through 25 August. The immature stages are unknown.
</paragraph>
